"signal_description": "The SIGNAL query is selecting data from the 'defaultview-225' table. It retrieves the 'Inv. Company Code Text' column. It also creates a new column named 'Inv Net Payment Terms period vs. Inv. Vendor Master NDD' which is based on a comparison between 'Last Inv. Item Net Payment Terms Period' and 'Last Inv. Item Vendor Master NDD'. If the 'Last Inv. Item Net Payment Terms Period' is less than 'Last Inv. Item Vendor Master NDD', it indicates that 'invoice payment terms are better than vendor payment terms'. If they are equal, it indicates that 'invoice payment terms are the same as vendor payment terms'. If 'Last Inv. Item Net Payment Terms Period' is greater than 'Last Inv. Item Vendor Master NDD', it indicates that 'invoice payment terms are worse than vendor payment terms'. If either or both of these columns are NULL, it will be indicated in the new column. If none of these conditions are met, the new column will simply contain 'ok'. The query also counts the number of case_id's and sums up the 'Inv. Converted USD Amount', naming these as 'No. Invoices' and '$ in Invoice' respectively. The result is then ordered by the fourth column in descending order."
